properties.areaDesc: East Slopes of the Washington Cascades
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 7 at 2:33PM PST until February 8 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Pendleton OR
properties.description:
...WINTER STORM TO BRING IMPACTFUL SNOW TO AREA MOUNTAINS TONIGHT
THROUGH SATURDAY...

.A storm system will approach the area from the northwest this
evening. A cold front will lower snow levels significantly
overnight and saturday leading to impactful snow for the
Washington Cascades and Blue Mountains of Oregon and Washington
through Saturday.

* WHAT...Snow expected for Western Kittitas County. Total snow
accumulations of 3 to 5 inches, but 6 to 12 inches near the
Cascade crest. Winds gusting as high as 40 mph.

* WHERE...East Slopes of the Washington Cascades.

* WHEN...From 4 PM Friday afternoon to 10 AM PST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. Gusty winds may
create blowing and drifting snow. Visibilities may be briefly
impaired.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling. If you must travel, be
prepared with warm clothes, food, water, and a flashlight.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1 or visiting wsdot.wa.gov.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM PST SATURDAY FOR WESTERN KITTITAS COUNTY
